            Moin moin!
            My name is Vinh, a master student of Quantitative
            Economics, majoring in statistics and econometrics, from
            Kiel University.
            This personal blog is a small project to apply what I’ve
            learned from lectures, books, and online courses. I use
            Python (pandas) for data wrangling and R
            (ggplot2) for data visualization.
            When not studying or working, I enjoy reading, playing
            guitar, taking pictures, traveling, and playing
            badminton.
            
            Education
            Kiel University | Kiel, Germany
            M.S. in Quantitative Economics | 2019 - 2022
            Foreign Trade University | Ho Chi Minh
            City, Vietnam
            B.S. in Business Administration | 2012 - 2016
